    • Constructor Detail

      • ExperimentCaseStoredBatchedInput

        protected ExperimentCaseStoredBatchedInput(String name,
                                InputStream input,
                                File holderDirectory,
                                boolean overwriteExisting)
                                    throws IOException,
                                           ExperimentDuplicationException
        Constructs the experiment case (file system based implementation) batched input
        Parameters:
        name - a String with the name for this input
        input - an InputStream with input data for the case batch, this input stream will be read and closed by this constructor and must correspond to zipped data
        holderDirectory - a File pointing to a directory relative to which this object save files, this directory must already exist
        overwriteExisting - if true, allows to overwrite the previously existing input file by the given name
        Throws:
        ExperimentDuplicationException - if the input must be new (overwriteExisting is false) but it already existed
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the input or persisting it
